
group theory: the mathematics of patterns and symmetry
  definition of group
  symmetry == invariance of set under group action
  generators
  subgroups
  
examples
  nonzero reals under multiplication
  integers under addition
  rotations of plane
  rotations and reflections of plane
  rotations, reflections, and translations of plane
  
  odd/even functions
  symmetries of polygons

  periodicity
  wallpaper
  
dynamics
  heat eqn, wave eqn
  fluids

activity
  verify that rotations of plane form a group
  
  compute multiplication table for symmetries of polygon
  express each element as product of generators